<center>
<h1>
Interactive Methods</h1></center>

<center>
<h2>
Summary</h2></center>

<ul>
<li>
Worksheets provide text based descriptions of the Image Processing tools</li>

<li>
At the end of the worksheet, the student has the opportunity to interactively
experiment with the operator</li>

<li>
A set of exercises provide guidance for the types of activities that should
be explored to learn more about the operator</li>

<li>
A workspace is available to allow combination of the operators that permits
more complex study of imagery</li>

<li>
After mastering the mechanics and utility of the operator; source code
is provided,&nbsp; allowing students to integrate these operations into
their own code.</li>
</ul>

